<bibRefCitation author="Oldroyd" box="[446,633,677,703]" firstAuthor="Oldroyd" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" refString="Oldroyd, H. (1970) Studies of African Asilidae (Diptera). 1. Asilidae of the Congo basin. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Entomology, Supplement, 24 (7), 207 - 334." type="journal article" year="1970">Oldroyd (1970)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,677,1063]" box="[198,801,717,743]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
Description of male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[555,662,717,743]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Figs 4–8</figureCitation>
: 
<typeStatus box="[673,788,717,743]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Holotype</typeStatus>
):
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,677,1063]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
Genital capsule rotated clockwise through approx. 90° (degree and direction probably not significant – see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardo" authorityYear="1925" box="[151,320,797,822]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Perasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transvaalensis">
<emphasis box="[151,320,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">transvaalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Epandrium in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[680,753,797,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than wide (length: breadth ration = 1: 1.07), in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[410,481,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) broad, with broadly rounded proximal and distal ends and slightly curved. Proctiger in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[397,468,877,903]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) clearly distally bilobed and projecting well beyond epandrial lobes. Hypandrium in ventral view tapering slightly to broadly curved distal end (
<figureCitation box="[891,964,917,943]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1428,917,943]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Figs 4–7</figureCitation>
) with somewhat rectangular appearance, dorsal lobe robust (hidden from view in dry condition); gonostylus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[305,375,997,1023]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with rounded apex bearing a slightly backwardly-directed dorsal spine. Aedeagal base in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[312,382,1037,1063]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) lacking distally directed projections.
</paragraph>
